00:16:52,185 --> 00:16:54,745
...and had an ungrateful nephew
put to sleep.

256
00:16:54,955 --> 00:16:57,423
l'm about at the end of my rope.

257
00:16:57,624 --> 00:17:00,388
Well, tie a noose in it
and slip it over your head.

258
00:17:04,064 --> 00:17:05,224
Damn it, Ouiser.

259
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,297
l don't wanna kill you.

260
00:17:09,002 --> 00:17:10,401
Boys, bring me my gun!

261
00:17:10,604 --> 00:17:14,700
Don't you threaten me, Drum Eatenton,
or l will call the police.

262
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:19,345
l gotta scare away about 5 zillion
birds before Shelby's reception.

263
00:17:19,546 --> 00:17:21,639
lf l don't, l'll have to deal
with my wife.

264
00:17:21,848 --> 00:17:24,043
l make it a point never
to deal with my wife.

265
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:27,084
That dog is on his last legs.
What'll l do with him?

266
00:17:27,287 --> 00:17:29,255
Serve him on toast.

267
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:34,784
Did you get those magnolias
out of my tree?

268
00:17:34,995 --> 00:17:37,862
The judge has not decided
whose tree that is exactly.

269
00:17:38,065 --> 00:17:39,396
lt is mine.

270
00:17:40,334 --> 00:17:43,064
l will speak to M'Lynn about this.

271
00:17:45,906 --> 00:17:48,431
Now, are these chocolate
chips semisweet or milk?

272
00:17:48,642 --> 00:17:49,666
They're milk.

273
00:17:49,876 --> 00:17:51,673
ls the Karo syrup light or dark?

274
00:17:51,878 --> 00:17:53,539
lt's a matter of taste.

275
00:17:53,747 --> 00:17:57,012
Where's the other one you were
talking about? ''Cuppa, Cuppa, Cuppa.''

276
00:17:57,217 --> 00:17:59,412
That's simple. You don't need
to write it down.

277
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,522
That's a cup of flour, a cup of sugar,
a cup of fruit cocktail with the juice.

278
00:18:03,724 --> 00:18:07,285
Then you mix and bake at 350
until gold and bubbly.

279
00:18:07,494 --> 00:18:09,291
-Sounds awfully rich.
-lt is.

280
00:18:09,496 --> 00:18:12,897
lt is. So l serve it over ice cream
to cut the sweetness.

281
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:14,962
l'll be right back, honey.

282
00:18:15,669 --> 00:18:18,160
M'Lynn, it looks like
you're ready to roll.

283
00:18:18,372 --> 00:18:21,000
And l think we can trust
Annelle here to do that.

284
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:23,836
Her coiffure card's
in a little box on the counter.

285
00:18:24,044 --> 00:18:26,410
l don't know.
Today is a very special day.

286
00:18:26,613 --> 00:18:28,774
My work is too pouffy
when l'm nervous.

287
00:18:28,982 --> 00:18:30,847
Stop that!
You're a professional now.

288
00:18:31,051 --> 00:18:34,043
So just get over there
and bang some hair.

289
00:18:37,524 --> 00:18:39,549
Does your dress have to go
over your head?

290
00:18:41,028 --> 00:18:42,017
No.

291
00:18:42,829 --> 00:18:43,818
Good.

292
00:18:45,232 --> 00:18:47,097
-l'm sorry.
-Relax.

293
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,597
You can't screw up her hair.

294
00:18:48,802 --> 00:18:51,703
Just tease it and make it look
like a brown football helmet.

295
00:18:51,905 --> 00:18:54,533
l must have missed the passage
in Emily Post that said:

296
00:18:54,741 --> 00:18:57,972
''All abuse is heaped
on the mother of the bride.''

297
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:00,237
Hush, girls.

298
00:19:00,447 --> 00:19:03,610
Your mama never tells us much.
What's Jackson like?

299
00:19:03,817 --> 00:19:04,909
He's really cute.

300
00:19:05,118 --> 00:19:09,179
l thought he was a pest at first, but
he kind of grew on me. Now l love him.

301
00:19:09,623 --> 00:19:11,887
You made a very good catch, Shelby.

302
00:19:12,092 --> 00:19:15,027
Louisiana lawyers do well,
whether they want to or not.

303
00:19:15,228 --> 00:19:16,525
l don't really care.

304
00:19:16,730 --> 00:19:19,494
Don't get me wrong.
The money is real nice and all.

305
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:23,329
But l just like the idea
of growing old with somebody.

306
00:19:24,071 --> 00:19:27,973
My dream is to sit on the porch,
covered with grandchildren, saying:

307
00:19:28,175 --> 00:19:30,439
''No!'' and ''Stop that!''

308
00:19:30,911 --> 00:19:32,572
Will you quit your nursing job?

309
00:19:32,779 --> 00:19:34,110
Never! l love it.

310
00:19:34,314 --> 00:19:36,839
l love being around all those babies.

311
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:40,918
Drum and l both feel that she should
not work after she gets married.

312
00:19:41,121 --> 00:19:45,080
l'm so anxious to discuss this topic
for the 900th time this week.

313
00:19:45,292 --> 00:19:49,388
You shouldn't be on your feet all day.
Be kind to your circulatory system.

314
00:19:49,930 --> 00:19:51,955
You know what you need in here, Truvy?

315
00:19:52,199 --> 00:19:53,461
You need a radio.

316
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:55,862
Music is a wonderful thing
in the background.

317
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:59,800
lt takes the pressure off everybody
feeling they have to talk so much.

318
00:20:00,006 --> 00:20:02,941
l used to have one, but l
slammed it against the wall...

319
00:20:03,143 --> 00:20:05,771
...when l couldn't figure out
where the batteries went.

320
00:20:05,979 --> 00:20:10,439
Of course, l know now l was suffering
from premenstrual syndrome.

321
00:20:11,518 --> 00:20:13,645
Radio? What did l just hear--?

322
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,114
Oh, yes.

323
00:20:15,655 --> 00:20:19,216
The Antilley family is selling KPPD.

324
00:20:19,726 --> 00:20:22,524
l wonder how much radio stations
sell for.

325
00:20:22,729 --> 00:20:23,889
Miss Clairee.

326
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:27,032
You should buy KPPD.
You got plenty of money.

327
00:20:27,234 --> 00:20:29,225
What would l do with a radio station?

328
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:33,270
Business never interested me.
Lloyd took care of that stuff.

329
00:20:34,641 --> 00:20:38,008
l hope you and Jackson will be
as happy as Lloyd and l were.

330
00:20:38,211 --> 00:20:40,805
We had such a good time.

331
00:20:41,314 --> 00:20:42,906
Until November.

332
00:20:45,018 --> 00:20:47,612
At least he hung on through
the state playoffs.

333
00:20:47,821 --> 00:20:50,813
Miss Clairee, there are still
good times to be had.

334
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:55,553
l really do love football.

335
00:20:55,929 --> 00:20:59,421
But it's hard to parlay that
into a reason to live.

336
00:21:00,834 --> 00:21:02,324
What are your colors, Shelby?

337
00:21:02,536 --> 00:21:04,902
They're ''blush'' and ''bashful.''

338
00:21:05,205 --> 00:21:07,469
Her colors are ''pink'' and ''pink.''

339
00:21:07,674 --> 00:21:10,802
My colors are blush and bashful, Mama.

340
00:21:11,011 --> 00:21:13,673
How precious is this wedding
gonna get, l ask you?

341
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:17,316
My colors are blush and bashful.
l have chosen two shades of pink.

342
00:21:17,517 --> 00:21:19,246
One is much deeper than the other.

343
00:21:19,452 --> 00:21:22,979
But the bridesmaids' dresses,
they are really beautiful.

344
00:21:23,290 --> 00:21:25,656
Ceremony will be too.

345
00:21:25,992 --> 00:21:29,155
The walls are banked with sprays
of flowers in my two shades...

346
00:21:29,362 --> 00:21:30,954
...of blush and bashful.

347
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:35,760
Pink carpets specially laid out for
my service, and pink silk bunting...

348
00:21:35,969 --> 00:21:38,301
...draped over anything
that would stand still.

349
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:41,440
lt looks like it's been
hosed down with Pepto-Bismol.

350
00:21:41,641 --> 00:21:45,133
l like pink. Pink is
my signature color.

351
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:46,570
How many bridesmaids?

352
00:21:47,180 --> 00:21:50,411
-Nine.
-Nine? Good Lord.

353
00:21:50,617 --> 00:21:54,451
Exactly. Mama made me have my cousins
and Margie St. Maurice.

354
00:21:54,654 --> 00:21:58,283
Let's not go into this now.
You know there was no way around it.

355
00:21:58,491 --> 00:21:59,822
lt will be pretentious.

356
00:22:00,293 --> 00:22:03,729
Daddy says, ''An ounce of pretension
is worth a pound of manure.''

357
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:06,228
The poet laureate of Dogwood Lane.

358
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:08,492
Mama, l wish you'd get off
Daddy's back.

359
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:11,535
-l don't wanna get into--
-Fill us in on the reception.

360
00:22:12,672 --> 00:22:15,140
My reception! My reception!

361
00:22:15,342 --> 00:22:20,279
Ferns, dancing, tons of people! Every
pink flower west of the Mississippi.

362
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:23,608
Wedding cake in the dining room
and the groom's cake....

363
00:22:24,117 --> 00:22:25,982
Hidden in the carport?

364
00:22:26,686 --> 00:22:28,950
Shelby and l, we agree on one thing.

365
00:22:29,155 --> 00:22:30,645
The groom's cake.

366
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:33,257
lt's awful.

367
00:22:33,693 --> 00:22:36,355
lt's in the shape
of a giant armadillo.

368
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:39,589
An armadillo? You're joking, right?

369
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:44,259
No. Jackson wanted a cake in the shape
of an armadillo. His aunt makes them.

370
00:22:44,471 --> 00:22:45,631
lt's unusual.

371
00:22:45,839 --> 00:22:47,101
lt's repulsive.

372
00:22:47,307 --> 00:22:49,207
lt's got gray icing.

373
00:22:49,409 --> 00:22:52,310
l can't even begin to think
how you'd make gray icing.

374
00:22:52,512 --> 00:22:56,676
Worse, the cake part is
red velvet cake. Blood red.

375
00:22:56,883 --> 00:23:01,217
People will hack into this poor animal
that looks like it's bleeding to death.

376
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:03,548
The rehearsal supper was
a real experience.

377
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:05,850
Mama, it wasn't that bad.

378
00:23:06,226 --> 00:23:08,751
lt was out at Jackson's
uncle's place on the river.

379
00:23:08,962 --> 00:23:10,953
He comes from the good
old Southern family...

380
00:23:11,164 --> 00:23:14,600
...with good old Southern values.
You shoot it, stuff it or marry it.

381
00:23:15,702 --> 00:23:17,727
They're simply outdoorsy, that's all.

382
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:21,032
Did y'all do anything
especially romantic?

383
00:23:21,241 --> 00:23:24,506
We drove down to Frenchmen's Point
and went parking.

384
00:23:25,745 --> 00:23:28,179
Oh, Shelby. Really!

385
00:23:28,882 --> 00:23:31,749
M'Lynn, leave her alone.
This is my favorite part.

386
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:35,752
This is the romantic part. See,
that's what really melts my butter.

387
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:40,552
Then we went skinny dipping, and we did
things that frightened the fish.

388
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:43,923
lt's been a long time since we've had
a youngster in this place.

389
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:46,155
We talked and talked and talked....

390
00:23:46,366 --> 00:23:50,769
l love those kind of talks
in the arms of the man you love.

391
00:23:51,137 --> 00:23:53,264
Actually, we fought most of the time.

392
00:23:53,473 --> 00:23:54,940
You fought?

393
00:23:55,342 --> 00:23:57,173
l told him l wouldn't marry him.

394
00:23:57,978 --> 00:23:58,808
What?

395
00:23:59,446 --> 00:24:01,209
Why'd you go do a thing like that?

396
00:24:01,414 --> 00:24:03,939
lt's okay now. We worked it all out.

397
00:24:04,751 --> 00:24:08,346
lt's probably just one of those
last-minute jitter things.

398
00:24:08,555 --> 00:24:10,386
No, but the wedding's still on.

399
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:11,989
Well, thank goodness.

400
00:24:12,192 --> 00:24:16,253
Because this is going
in the Hairdo Hall of Fame.

401
00:24:16,463 --> 00:24:20,092
Shelby, you scared us. That wasn't
a nice thing to do to your mama.

402
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:24,293
Never say that to a woman who's
marinating 50 pounds of crab claws.

403
00:24:25,171 --> 00:24:28,334
But the making up can be so romantic.

404
00:24:30,076 --> 00:24:32,044
l miss romance so much.

405
00:24:32,245 --> 00:24:34,770
Truvy, it can't be that bad.

406
00:24:34,981 --> 00:24:35,970
Oh, really, now?

407
00:24:36,182 --> 00:24:40,243
The last romantic thing my husband
did for me was back in 1 972.

408
00:24:40,453 --> 00:24:43,547
He enclosed this carport
so l could support him.

409
00:24:43,757 --> 00:24:46,749
l think l have something
that could cheer you up.

410
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:50,726
Drum and l plan to talk to your husband
about adding on to our house.

411
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:52,158
M'Lynn, are you serious?

412
00:24:52,365 --> 00:24:55,198
lf you give Spud a job,
l'll give you hot oil treatments...

413
00:24:55,402 --> 00:24:57,427
...for the rest of your life!

414
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:02,364
Annelle, this looks pretty good.
l think you know what you're doing.

415
00:25:02,575 --> 00:25:03,906
Thank you.

416
00:25:04,110 --> 00:25:06,408
Mrs. Eatenton, you have great hair.

417
00:25:06,613 --> 00:25:09,514
-Your scalp's as clean as a whistle.
-l try.

418
00:25:09,716 --> 00:25:11,013
lt must run in the family.

419
00:25:11,217 --> 00:25:15,677
This young'un's got the prettiest hair
l've ever had my hands in. So thick.

420
00:25:15,889 --> 00:25:19,347
Just because l'm bragging on you
don't mean you can get lazy on me.

421
00:25:19,559 --> 00:25:20,423
Stop it.

422
00:25:20,627 --> 00:25:21,457
Shelby?

423
00:25:22,228 --> 00:25:24,162
Shelby! M'Lynn!

424
00:25:26,032 --> 00:25:27,897
l'll get some juice.

425
00:25:29,469 --> 00:25:31,096
There's some candy in my purse.

426
00:25:31,304 --> 00:25:33,295
l have some right here.

427
00:25:34,674 --> 00:25:36,232
Shelby. Shelby.

428
00:25:36,443 --> 00:25:38,968
Hold on. Clairee's
getting you some juice.

429
00:25:40,413 --> 00:25:41,710
-Should l get her a cookie?
-No.

430
00:25:41,981 --> 00:25:42,811
Juice is better.

431
00:25:44,284 --> 00:25:45,410
Here's the juice.

432
00:25:46,686 --> 00:25:49,120
You need some juice.
You need some juice.

433
00:25:49,322 --> 00:25:51,290
-Stop it, Mama.
-Drink the juice.

434
00:25:51,491 --> 00:25:53,459
-Please drink the juice.
-No!

435
00:25:53,660 --> 00:25:55,992
Stop it! l have
some candy in my purse.

436
00:25:56,196 --> 00:25:57,823
You didn't bring your purse.

437
00:25:58,031 --> 00:26:00,022
You didn't bring your purse.
No, you didn't.

438
00:26:00,233 --> 00:26:02,326
No, here you go. There you go.

439
00:26:02,535 --> 00:26:04,093
Drink some of this.

440
00:26:05,772 --> 00:26:07,239
lt's not any wonder...

441
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:10,068
...with all this running around
and wedding nonsense.

442
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:14,141
Excuse me. Should l call
the doctor or something?

443
00:26:14,347 --> 00:26:15,405
She's a diabetic.

444
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:18,209
She just has a little too much
insulin, that's all.

445
00:26:18,418 --> 00:26:21,080
We'll get a little more in her.
She'll be all right.

446
00:26:21,521 --> 00:26:24,183
lf you don't leave me alone,
l'm gonna leave.

447
00:26:24,390 --> 00:26:27,655
l'd love to see you try.
Cooperate, please.

448
00:26:27,861 --> 00:26:29,658
Honey, drink. Please.

449
00:26:29,863 --> 00:26:31,524
Come on, now. Thattagirl.

450
00:26:31,731 --> 00:26:33,323
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

451
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:35,761
There you go. There you go.

452
00:26:36,002 --> 00:26:38,095
There, there. That's a start.

453
00:26:38,338 --> 00:26:40,499
This one hit her fast.

454
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:43,206
She's been so upset lately.

455
00:26:44,210 --> 00:26:47,077
Dr. Mitchell told her
on her last appointment...

456
00:26:48,781 --> 00:26:50,180
...children aren't possible.

457
00:26:52,218 --> 00:26:55,278
Don't talk about me like l'm not here.

458
00:26:57,624 --> 00:27:00,650
She's making some sense now.
Yes, she is.

459
00:27:01,494 --> 00:27:04,691
This one was not bad at all.
lt was not bad at all.

460
00:27:04,898 --> 00:27:07,366
l think we need
a little more juice.

461
00:27:07,567 --> 00:27:09,432
Could l do something to help?

462
00:27:09,636 --> 00:27:10,728
No, no.

463
00:27:10,937 --> 00:27:12,928
She'll be fine.
Don't fuss over her.

464
00:27:13,139 --> 00:27:15,004
Normality's very important to Shelby.

465
00:27:15,208 --> 00:27:16,698
-Here, M'Lynn.
-Thanks.

466
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:20,245
l'm really sorry about
the children part, M'Lynn.

467
00:27:20,446 --> 00:27:21,572
l know.

468
00:27:21,881 --> 00:27:25,510
She's afraid Jackson will be throwing
away his chance to have children.

469
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:29,420
Jackson said:

470
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:33,291
''Shelby, don't be stupid.

471
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,758
There's plenty of kids out there
need good homes.''

472
00:27:36,963 --> 00:27:38,191
Drink some.

473
00:27:41,467 --> 00:27:45,096
''We'll adopt 1 0 of them.
We'll buy them if we have to.''

474
00:27:45,438 --> 00:27:47,838
Jackson sounds like good people to me.

475
00:27:56,816 --> 00:28:00,047
-Mama, l'm sorry.
-That's all right, honey.

476
00:28:00,253 --> 00:28:03,051
lt's all right.
lt's all over now. lt's all--

477
00:28:03,256 --> 00:28:04,883
You hold your juice.

478
00:28:06,125 --> 00:28:07,092
lt's all over.

479
00:28:07,293 --> 00:28:09,523
Hold your juice, all right?

480
00:28:11,497 --> 00:28:12,725
You all right?

481
00:28:13,833 --> 00:28:15,767
-Truvy, l'm sorry.
-l'll fix it.

482
00:28:16,436 --> 00:28:18,267
We'll fix it.

483
00:28:27,614 --> 00:28:30,082
-What did l do with my gun?
-Where'd you leave it?

484
00:28:30,283 --> 00:28:32,012
How the hell do l know?

485
00:28:33,953 --> 00:28:36,581
Come on, we have work to do.
Daylight's burning.

486
00:28:37,023 --> 00:28:38,923
We're gonna get rid of some birds!

487
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:47,495
-Got the arrows, Daddy.
-All right.

488
00:28:48,368 --> 00:28:50,233
Look here. Look here.

489
00:28:52,605 --> 00:28:55,836
-l got the targets.
-We're not going target shooting.

490
00:28:57,577 --> 00:29:00,011
Miss Clairee, what cute shoes!

491
00:29:00,213 --> 00:29:01,407
You think so?

492
00:29:01,614 --> 00:29:03,605
l'm not so sure myself.

493
00:29:04,150 --> 00:29:06,141
They seem a little too racy for me.

494
00:29:06,352 --> 00:29:07,649
l'll probably give them away.

495
00:29:07,854 --> 00:29:09,981
They're just too ''cha-cha'' for words.

496
00:29:10,189 --> 00:29:12,453
lf you decide to get rid of them,
