Our little Annelle here has become
one of the hottest tickets in town.

750
00:49:38,884 --> 00:49:40,146
lt's true.

751
00:49:40,685 --> 00:49:45,315
l am enjoying the city more, and l'm so
excited about this Christmas festival.

752
00:49:45,524 --> 00:49:47,788
There's a Messiah sing-along tomorrow.

753
00:49:48,460 --> 00:49:51,452
-What's the matter?
-Nobody move! Nobody move!

754
00:49:51,663 --> 00:49:53,153
My contact!

755
00:49:53,999 --> 00:49:56,160
-Stay back. Stay back.
-Don't move!

756
00:49:56,368 --> 00:49:57,665
Can you back up, please?

757
00:49:57,869 --> 00:49:59,336
Hello, darlings!

758
00:49:59,538 --> 00:50:01,233
When did you get into town?

759
00:50:01,439 --> 00:50:02,872
This afternoon.

760
00:50:03,241 --> 00:50:04,708
Here. Merry Christmas.

761
00:50:04,910 --> 00:50:08,346
l'm showing Jackson everything.
He's never been to the festival.

762
00:50:08,547 --> 00:50:10,947
Make sure you listen
to the football game tonight.

763
00:50:11,149 --> 00:50:12,514
What are we listening for?

764
00:50:12,717 --> 00:50:15,379
Me. l'm a working gal now.
Didn't your mama tell you?

765
00:50:15,587 --> 00:50:17,680
Mama never tells anyone anything.

766
00:50:17,889 --> 00:50:20,619
l'm the color announcer
for the Devils. l'm fabulous.

767
00:50:20,825 --> 00:50:23,259
l'm just too colorful for words.

768
00:50:23,461 --> 00:50:25,122
Nice of them to let you
on the radio.

769
00:50:25,330 --> 00:50:29,130
Nice, nothing.
l own the radio station.

770
00:50:29,334 --> 00:50:30,596
-You bought it?
-Yes.

771
00:50:30,802 --> 00:50:32,167
KPPD...

772
00:50:32,504 --> 00:50:35,598
...the station of choice
in Chinquapin Parish.

773
00:50:35,807 --> 00:50:37,104
Mrs. Belcher, we've gotta go!

774
00:50:37,309 --> 00:50:39,140
-Bye!
-Kickoff!

775
00:50:53,959 --> 00:50:55,153
Well?

776
00:50:58,463 --> 00:51:00,658
Rolly Bassett got the contract.

777
00:51:01,166 --> 00:51:03,100
His bid was 6000 under mine.

778
00:51:03,301 --> 00:51:04,768
Six thousand?

779
00:51:06,538 --> 00:51:09,632
He owns all his own equipment
and l don't.

780
00:51:12,711 --> 00:51:15,179
lt's hell to be poor and hired out.

781
00:51:16,648 --> 00:51:20,812
l have got some fried chicken here,
prepared by Christian women...

782
00:51:21,019 --> 00:51:22,418
...a bottle of cheap wine...

783
00:51:22,621 --> 00:51:26,352
...and l've arranged for some
pretty incredible fireworks.

784
00:51:28,326 --> 00:51:29,657
Come on, Spud.

785
00:51:29,861 --> 00:51:34,423
l don't wanna miss the Nativity made
entirely out of sparklers.

786
00:51:35,867 --> 00:51:40,065
-l don't feel much like it.
-You will once we get there.

787
00:51:41,272 --> 00:51:43,365
l'm happy where l am.

788
00:51:47,312 --> 00:51:50,338
We always watch the fireworks.

789
00:51:52,917 --> 00:51:55,442
This is KPPD radio...

790
00:51:55,654 --> 00:51:58,521
...station of choice
in Chinquapin Parish...

791
00:51:58,723 --> 00:52:02,215
...coming to you live
from the Devils' locker room.

792
00:52:02,427 --> 00:52:06,989
This is Bark Boone
with color announcer Clairee Belcher.

793
00:52:07,198 --> 00:52:08,790
Thank you, Bark.

794
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:12,128
You know, it's a shame
our listeners can't be here...

795
00:52:12,537 --> 00:52:15,665
...to see the gorgeous
new Devil uniform.

796
00:52:16,841 --> 00:52:18,001
They're lovely.

797
00:52:18,209 --> 00:52:21,178
l myself would never have chosen
those white pants.

798
00:52:21,379 --> 00:52:24,610
l would've gone with a darker color.
White shows everything.

799
00:52:24,816 --> 00:52:27,979
Just look at those grass stains.
lmpossible to get out.

800
00:52:28,186 --> 00:52:31,087
lt's hard to keep white clean
when you're tackled.

801
00:52:31,289 --> 00:52:32,881
But l love the tops.

802
00:52:33,091 --> 00:52:34,183
Such a vibrant purple.

803
00:52:34,392 --> 00:52:37,327
Bark, would you call this color
grape or aubergine?

804
00:52:37,529 --> 00:52:38,826
Shut up!

805
00:52:39,197 --> 00:52:40,027
What?

806
00:52:40,231 --> 00:52:42,722
You're making a fool out of yourself.

807
00:52:42,934 --> 00:52:43,923
l am not!

808
00:52:44,135 --> 00:52:45,432
This is football.

809
00:52:45,637 --> 00:52:48,731
All people wanna hear about
is touchdowns and injuries.

810
00:52:48,940 --> 00:52:51,568
They don't give a damn
about that grape shit.

811
00:52:52,177 --> 00:52:55,237
We have a new psychiatrist
that comes in two days a week.

812
00:52:55,447 --> 00:52:58,314
Of course, l pick her name
out of the grab bag.

813
00:52:58,516 --> 00:53:02,350
l've gotta get something for her.
Would you put that on the list?

814
00:53:02,587 --> 00:53:06,455
l have no idea
what to get your father.

815
00:53:07,058 --> 00:53:09,219
What's Jackson giving you?
Do you know?

816
00:53:10,795 --> 00:53:11,625
Furniture.

817
00:53:12,964 --> 00:53:14,693
Furniture? Well, my!

818
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:18,833
Must be nice to be married
to a rich lawyer.

819
00:53:19,671 --> 00:53:20,933
For the living room?

820
00:53:22,574 --> 00:53:23,802
No, for the nursery.

821
00:53:28,580 --> 00:53:33,210
We wanted to tell you when you and
Daddy were together, but you never are.

822
00:53:33,418 --> 00:53:35,079
lt's every man for himself.

823
00:53:37,322 --> 00:53:38,448
l'm pregnant.

824
00:53:41,960 --> 00:53:43,484
l realize that.

825
00:53:46,998 --> 00:53:48,465
ls that it?

826
00:53:49,534 --> 00:53:50,967
ls that all you're gonna say?

827
00:53:52,470 --> 00:53:54,438
What do you want me to say?

828
00:53:55,707 --> 00:53:58,175
Something along the lines of
''Congratulations.''

829
00:54:01,246 --> 00:54:02,474
Congratulations.

830
00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:17,193
Would it be too much to ask...

831
00:54:18,997 --> 00:54:20,624
...for a little excitement?

832
00:54:20,832 --> 00:54:24,268
Not too much. l wouldn't want you
to break a sweat or anything.

833
00:54:29,607 --> 00:54:31,097
lt's in July.

834
00:54:37,982 --> 00:54:40,041
You have to help me plan.

835
00:54:42,086 --> 00:54:43,678
We're gonna get a new house.

836
00:54:43,888 --> 00:54:46,550
Jackson and l are going
house hunting next week.

837
00:54:47,158 --> 00:54:48,955
He loves to hunt for anything.

838
00:54:49,460 --> 00:54:52,987
-What does Jackson say about all this?
-He's so excited.

839
00:54:54,365 --> 00:54:57,425
He says he doesn't care
whether it's a boy or a girl...

840
00:54:57,635 --> 00:55:00,934
...but l know he really wants
a son so bad he can taste it.

841
00:55:02,273 --> 00:55:04,707
He's cute about it.
lt's all he talks about.

842
00:55:04,909 --> 00:55:06,342
''Jackson Latcherie, Jr.''

843
00:55:06,544 --> 00:55:07,841
Does he ever listen?

844
00:55:08,513 --> 00:55:11,209
When doctors and specialists
give you advice...

845
00:55:11,583 --> 00:55:12,811
...does he listen?

846
00:55:13,017 --> 00:55:14,746
l know you never do. Does he?

847
00:55:20,258 --> 00:55:21,088
What?

848
00:55:24,696 --> 00:55:28,996
l guess since he doesn't have to carry
the baby, it isn't any of his concern.

849
00:55:31,870 --> 00:55:33,861
l want a child.

850
00:55:34,439 --> 00:55:36,999
What about adoption?
You filled out applications.

851
00:55:37,208 --> 00:55:41,645
No judge is going to give a baby
to someone with my medical record.

852
00:55:44,415 --> 00:55:46,508
Jackson put out feelers
about buying one.

853
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:48,379
People do it all the time.

854
00:55:51,155 --> 00:55:52,622
Listen to me.

855
00:55:54,826 --> 00:55:56,760
l want a child of my own.

856
00:56:01,599 --> 00:56:03,726
l think it would help things a lot.

857
00:56:13,511 --> 00:56:14,910
l see.

858
00:56:27,992 --> 00:56:30,085
You worry too much.

859
00:56:31,663 --> 00:56:36,191
l never worry, because l always know
you're worried enough for both of us.

860
00:56:41,873 --> 00:56:44,307
Jackson and l gave this
a lot of thought.

861
00:56:44,509 --> 00:56:48,411
-There's a first time for everything.
-Don't start on Jackson.

862
00:56:48,613 --> 00:56:52,709
Your body has been through so much.
Why would you do this to yourself?

863
00:56:52,917 --> 00:56:57,183
-Diabetics have healthy babies.
-You are special, Shelby.

864
00:56:57,889 --> 00:57:00,551
There are limits to what you can do.

865
00:57:07,832 --> 00:57:09,697
l am going to be...

866
00:57:10,368 --> 00:57:12,199
...very, very careful.

867
00:57:13,404 --> 00:57:16,339
Nobody's gonna be hurt
or disappointed...

868
00:57:16,541 --> 00:57:18,099
...or even inconvenienced.

869
00:57:18,977 --> 00:57:21,673
Least of all Jackson, l'm sure.

870
00:57:25,583 --> 00:57:26,777
You're jealous.

871
00:57:27,952 --> 00:57:30,546
You no longer have
a say-so in what l do...

872
00:57:30,755 --> 00:57:32,950
...and that drives you up the wall.

873
00:57:34,092 --> 00:57:37,960
You're ready to spit nails
because you can't call the shots.

874
00:57:39,197 --> 00:57:42,598
l did not raise my daughter
to talk to me like this.

875
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:47,566
-Yes, you did.
-No, l didn't.

876
00:57:47,972 --> 00:57:52,136
Whenever we asked what you wanted
for us when we grew up, what'd you say?

877
00:57:52,343 --> 00:57:54,038
l'm not in the mood to play games.

878
00:57:54,245 --> 00:57:56,770
Just tell me what you said.
What did you say?

879
00:57:56,981 --> 00:58:00,815
The only thing l have ever said to you
is that l want you to be happy.

880
00:58:02,286 --> 00:58:05,813
The one thing that would make me happy
is to have a baby.

881
00:58:06,891 --> 00:58:09,860
lf l could adopt one, l would,
but l can't.

882
00:58:12,196 --> 00:58:16,155
l'm going to have a baby,
and l wish you'd be happy too.

883
00:58:17,135 --> 00:58:19,103
l'll tell you what l wish.

884
00:58:21,039 --> 00:58:22,904
l don't know what l wish.

885
00:58:26,377 --> 00:58:29,403
l don't know why you have to make
everything so difficult.

886
00:58:32,417 --> 00:58:36,478
l look at having this baby
as the opportunity of a lifetime.

887
00:58:36,821 --> 00:58:40,450
Sure, there may be risk involved,
but that's true for anybody.

888
00:58:41,426 --> 00:58:43,986
But you get through it
and life goes on.

889
00:58:44,429 --> 00:58:47,557
When all's said and done,
there'll be a piece of immortality...

890
00:58:47,765 --> 00:58:51,030
...with Jackson's good looks
and my sense of style, l hope.

891
00:58:52,270 --> 00:58:53,202
Please.

892
00:58:53,638 --> 00:58:54,935
Please.

893
00:58:56,407 --> 00:58:58,238
l need your support.

894
00:59:00,745 --> 00:59:03,805
l would rather have 30 minutes
of wonderful...

895
00:59:04,015 --> 00:59:06,540
...than a lifetime of nothing special.

896
00:59:25,069 --> 00:59:27,560
l'll hand it to you.
l don't wanna hit you.

897
00:59:27,772 --> 00:59:30,673
-Okay, l got one hole left.
-Right.

898
00:59:31,042 --> 00:59:34,307
Put the cords so they don't show.
lt'll look tacky.

899
00:59:34,512 --> 00:59:36,480
You told me about 40 times.

900
00:59:40,251 --> 00:59:41,650
Did you do all this?

901
00:59:42,053 --> 00:59:43,247
Guilty.

902
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:47,083
Truvy just turned over
the decoration responsibility to me.

903
00:59:47,458 --> 00:59:51,690
l went to the fire sale at the Baptist
Bookstore in Shreveport last week.

904
00:59:51,896 --> 00:59:55,127
They had mismatched manger scenes
at incredibly low prices.

905
00:59:55,333 --> 00:59:59,360
l cleaned them out of baby Jesuses,
which l made into ornaments.

906
00:59:59,570 --> 01:00:00,434
Ready to roll.

907
01:00:00,638 --> 01:00:02,299
Shelby, would you do the honors?

908
01:00:06,210 --> 01:00:09,179
-Here you are, Mrs. Latcherie.
-Thanks, Sammy.

909
01:00:09,881 --> 01:00:10,905
Ready?

910
01:00:16,254 --> 01:00:18,279
Annelle, it's wonderful!

911
01:00:18,489 --> 01:00:19,751
lt works!

912
01:00:20,024 --> 01:00:22,049
How cute!

913
01:00:22,660 --> 01:00:25,458
l think your elves have gone berserk.

914
01:00:25,963 --> 01:00:28,761
Shelby! l wasn't expecting
to see you here today.

915
01:00:28,966 --> 01:00:32,663
l'm running a special.
lt's called a ''Christmas quickie.''

916
01:00:32,870 --> 01:00:36,931
l'm beyond help. l've discovered
the early stages of crow's feet.

917
01:00:37,141 --> 01:00:41,601
Time marches on, and eventually you
realize it's marching across your face.

918
01:00:41,812 --> 01:00:43,746
-Stop it.
-Oh, no.

919
01:00:44,248 --> 01:00:45,374
lt's Miss Ouiser.

920
01:00:49,787 --> 01:00:52,847
l'm supposed to give her
a pedicure today.

921
01:00:53,057 --> 01:00:54,922
l hate working on her feet.

922
01:00:55,126 --> 01:00:58,823
lt could've been worse.
She could've wanted a bikini waxing.

923
01:00:59,463 --> 01:01:02,227
-Let's not get graphic.
-Why not?

924
01:01:02,433 --> 01:01:05,061
Miss Ouiser, l met
an old friend of yours.

925
01:01:06,270 --> 01:01:07,601
Owen Jenkins.

926
01:01:09,140 --> 01:01:12,405
Owen! Now, there's a blast
from the past.

927
01:01:12,610 --> 01:01:14,305
You remember him?
He remembers you.

928
01:01:14,512 --> 01:01:17,709
Of course. He had the longest
nose hair in the free world.

929
01:01:17,915 --> 01:01:20,941
He doesn't now.
He hardly has any hair anywhere.

930
01:01:21,152 --> 01:01:23,950
Owen's been gone from Chinquapin
since God was a boy.

931
01:01:24,155 --> 01:01:25,383
l forgot he existed.

932
01:01:25,790 --> 01:01:28,258
He lives in Monroe
and goes to First Presbyterian.

933
01:01:28,659 --> 01:01:31,560
He found out where l was from
and asked if l knew you.

934
01:01:32,129 --> 01:01:33,790
He used to live in Ohio.

935
01:01:33,998 --> 01:01:37,024
His wife just died recently,
and he's moved back down here.

936
01:01:38,803 --> 01:01:40,464
Does this story have a point?

937
01:01:40,671 --> 01:01:44,402
No, not really. He just
remembers you fondly, l think.

938
01:01:44,609 --> 01:01:45,906
l can't imagine why.

939
01:01:46,244 --> 01:01:49,509
He was not a bad fellow.
But l managed to run him off...

940
01:01:49,714 --> 01:01:51,944
...and marry the first
of two deadbeats.

941
01:01:52,149 --> 01:01:55,084
Maybe l could arrange for us all
to get together.

942
01:01:55,553 --> 01:01:57,612
-Maybe not.
-Why not?

943
01:01:59,023 --> 01:02:03,289
ln a few decades, l married the two
most worthless men in the universe...

944
01:02:03,494 --> 01:02:07,988
...and proceeded to have the three most
ungrateful children ever conceived.

945
01:02:08,266 --> 01:02:10,393
The only reason people are
nice to me...

946
01:02:10,601 --> 01:02:12,899
...is because l have
more money than God.

947
01:02:13,104 --> 01:02:15,629
l'm not about to open
a new can of worms.

948
01:02:17,441 --> 01:02:18,271
What?

949
01:02:18,909 --> 01:02:21,309
lf this is how you feel,
it isn't healthy.

950
01:02:21,879 --> 01:02:25,838
Maybe you should come down to the
Guidance Center and talk to someone.

951
01:02:26,450 --> 01:02:28,577
l'm not crazy, M'Lynn.

952
01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:32,153
l've just been in a very bad mood
for 40 years.

953
01:02:38,129 --> 01:02:39,426
Merry Christmas.

954
01:02:39,630 --> 01:02:41,461
Look at you. ls that new?

955
01:02:41,666 --> 01:02:44,430
l made the dress
with my own two hands.

956
01:02:44,635 --> 01:02:46,762
l just threw the rest of it together.

957
01:02:46,971 --> 01:02:49,769
The only thing that separates us
from the animals...

958
01:02:49,974 --> 01:02:52,499
...is our ability to accessorize.

959
01:02:53,477 --> 01:02:55,240
Annelle, why are you so late?

960
01:02:55,446 --> 01:02:58,813
Did you and Sammy get tangled up
in the tinsel?

961
01:02:59,016 --> 01:03:01,348
Truvy, you kill me.

962
01:03:01,619 --> 01:03:03,314
-Merry Christmas.
-Thank you.

963
01:03:03,521 --> 01:03:05,546
-Merry Christmas to you.
-Oh, darling.

964
01:03:05,756 --> 01:03:10,022
Your nephew Marshall is a little piece
of heaven right here on earth.

965
01:03:10,227 --> 01:03:12,923
They're family and l love them,
but they do look like...

966
01:03:13,130 --> 01:03:15,564
...they've all been carved
out of cream cheese.

967
01:03:18,636 --> 01:03:22,470
Clairee, l'm surprised at you
talking about your kin that way.

968
01:03:22,673 --> 01:03:24,368
As somebody always said:

969
01:03:24,575 --> 01:03:28,671
''lf you can't say anything nice
about anybody, come sit by me.''

970
01:03:28,879 --> 01:03:29,811
That's a good one.

971
01:03:35,486 --> 01:03:38,148
-Somebody wants to see you.
-Who?

972
01:03:38,356 --> 01:03:40,756
l've opened the can of worms for you.

973
01:03:44,095 --> 01:03:45,323
Hell.

974
01:03:45,696 --> 01:03:46,822
Owen Jenkins.

975
01:03:47,031 --> 01:03:49,261
Hello, Louisa. Remember me?

976
01:03:50,434 --> 01:03:53,335
My God, you look different.
Have you shrunk?

977
01:03:55,506 --> 01:03:58,907
You look terrific.
You've hardly changed at all.

978
01:03:59,744 --> 01:04:02,235
l'm not as sweet as l used to be.

979
01:04:12,823 --> 01:04:14,950
l cannot believe Shelby did that.

980
01:04:15,159 --> 01:04:16,251
Owen.

981
01:04:16,460 --> 01:04:18,189
After all these years.

982
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:20,921
l'm not sure l can be
gracious under pressure.

983
01:04:21,132 --> 01:04:23,794
Shelby does a lot of things
l can't believe.

984
01:04:24,668 --> 01:04:28,399
What's wrong with you these days?
You got a reindeer up your butt?

985
01:04:28,606 --> 01:04:30,005
Everybody!

986
01:04:30,207 --> 01:04:32,698
Tommy, get all these people outside.

987
01:04:36,514 --> 01:04:40,041
Quiet down. l just want
a moment of your time, folks.

988
01:04:42,353 --> 01:04:44,287
Today, my daughter...

989
01:04:44,822 --> 01:04:46,983
...told me a big secret.

990
01:04:47,558 --> 01:04:51,460
Now, don't worry, honey, l'm not
gonna tell them your pregnant.

991
01:04:54,098 --> 01:04:56,931
l'm just gonna tell them
l'm gonna be a granddaddy.

992
01:04:57,835 --> 01:04:59,666
That's wonderful!

