01:44:04,579 --> 01:44:05,705
l'm fine.

1484
01:44:05,914 --> 01:44:08,075
l'm fine. l'm fine.

1485
01:44:08,383 --> 01:44:09,873
l'm fine!

1486
01:44:12,354 --> 01:44:14,845
l could jog all the way
to Texas and back...

1487
01:44:15,390 --> 01:44:17,858
...but my daughter can't.

1488
01:44:18,360 --> 01:44:20,089
She never could.

1489
01:44:20,295 --> 01:44:23,423
God! l'm so mad,
l don't know what to do!

1490
01:44:23,632 --> 01:44:24,656
l wanna know why.

1491
01:44:24,866 --> 01:44:27,699
l wanna know why
Shelby's life is over.

1492
01:44:27,903 --> 01:44:32,237
l wanna know how that baby will ever
know how wonderful his mother was.

1493
01:44:32,440 --> 01:44:35,841
Will he ever know what she
went through for him?

1494
01:44:36,044 --> 01:44:38,842
Oh, God, l wanna know why!

1495
01:44:39,047 --> 01:44:40,514
Why?!

1496
01:44:41,216 --> 01:44:44,083
Lord, l wish l could understand.

1497
01:44:47,389 --> 01:44:49,016
lt's not supposed to happen this way.

1498
01:44:49,224 --> 01:44:52,216
l'm supposed to go first.
l've always been ready to go.

1499
01:44:53,628 --> 01:44:55,289
l don't think l can take this.

1500
01:44:55,497 --> 01:44:57,260
l don't think l can take this.

1501
01:44:57,465 --> 01:45:00,457
l just wanna hit somebody
till they feel as bad as l do.

1502
01:45:00,669 --> 01:45:03,729
l just wanna hit something.
l wanna hit it hard!

1503
01:45:05,173 --> 01:45:06,140
Here.

1504
01:45:06,775 --> 01:45:07,969
Hit this.

1505
01:45:08,577 --> 01:45:10,477
Go ahead. Slap her!

1506
01:45:10,745 --> 01:45:12,542
-Are you crazy?
-Hit her!

1507
01:45:12,747 --> 01:45:15,773
-Are you high, Clairee?
-Have you lost your mind?

1508
01:45:15,984 --> 01:45:19,886
We'll sell T-shirts saying,
''l Slapped Ouiser Boudreaux''!

1509
01:45:20,088 --> 01:45:20,986
Hit her!

1510
01:45:21,189 --> 01:45:22,622
Miss Clairee, enough.

1511
01:45:22,924 --> 01:45:27,384
Ouiser, this is your chance to do
something for your fellow man.

1512
01:45:27,696 --> 01:45:28,890
Knock her lights out!

1513
01:45:29,097 --> 01:45:30,826
Let go of me!

1514
01:45:31,166 --> 01:45:34,897
You missed the chance of a lifetime.
Half of Chinquapin would give...

1515
01:45:35,103 --> 01:45:37,628
...their eyeteeth
to take a whack at Ouiser.

1516
01:45:47,616 --> 01:45:49,641
You are a pig from hell!

1517
01:45:54,256 --> 01:45:55,951
Ouiser, don't leave!

1518
01:45:56,725 --> 01:45:58,818
l was just kidding. Come back!

1519
01:46:03,598 --> 01:46:05,862
That was not a very
Christian thing to do.

1520
01:46:06,067 --> 01:46:08,399
Annelle, you gotta lighten up.

1521
01:46:46,274 --> 01:46:47,366
Go away.

1522
01:46:47,575 --> 01:46:50,840
Okay, all right. Hit me, then.
l deserve it.

1523
01:46:51,046 --> 01:46:53,310
You are evil,
and you must be destroyed.

1524
01:46:53,515 --> 01:46:56,712
Mother Nature's taking care of that
faster than you could.

1525
01:46:56,918 --> 01:46:59,853
Things were getting entirely
too serious for a moment.

1526
01:47:00,055 --> 01:47:01,522
We needed to laugh.

1527
01:47:03,458 --> 01:47:06,086
l bet Lloyd got a kick out of it.

1528
01:47:06,761 --> 01:47:11,255
Lloyd got a great deal of enjoyment
at my expense when he was alive.

1529
01:47:12,500 --> 01:47:15,663
You know l love you
more than my luggage.

1530
01:47:28,416 --> 01:47:30,281
This is my bench.

1531
01:47:30,652 --> 01:47:32,643
Get off my bench!

1532
01:47:33,388 --> 01:47:35,822
Get off my--!
Good. Now, sit.

1533
01:47:36,024 --> 01:47:39,118
You are too twisted for color TV.

1534
01:47:40,395 --> 01:47:42,226
Have your roots done.

1535
01:47:47,969 --> 01:47:51,632
l shouldn't have gone on
the way l did. l made everybody cry.

1536
01:47:51,840 --> 01:47:55,332
Don't be silly. Laughter through
tears is my favorite emotion.

1537
01:47:55,543 --> 01:47:56,908
Thanks, Annelle.

1538
01:47:57,112 --> 01:48:00,309
Maybe l should have
an emotional outburst more often.

1539
01:48:00,515 --> 01:48:02,676
Maybe l should start
having them at home.

1540
01:48:02,884 --> 01:48:04,613
Drum would be so pleased.

1541
01:48:08,523 --> 01:48:11,856
Well, l'm glad to see
the two of you made up.

1542
01:48:12,060 --> 01:48:14,358
Ouiser can never stay mad at me.

1543
01:48:14,562 --> 01:48:17,554
She worships the quicksand l walk on.

1544
01:48:23,171 --> 01:48:24,297
You're in my prayers.

1545
01:48:31,312 --> 01:48:33,610
Yes, Annelle, l pray.

1546
01:48:35,683 --> 01:48:38,914
Well, l do. There, l said it.
l hope you're satisfied.

1547
01:48:39,287 --> 01:48:41,346
l have suspected this all along.

1548
01:48:41,723 --> 01:48:45,352
Don't you expect me to come
to one of your churches.

1549
01:48:45,560 --> 01:48:49,394
Those tent revivals with those
Bible-beaters doing God-knows-what.

1550
01:48:49,597 --> 01:48:52,361
They'd probably make me eat
a live chicken.

1551
01:48:52,767 --> 01:48:54,291
Not on your first visit.

1552
01:48:55,570 --> 01:48:57,435
Very good, Annelle.

1553
01:48:57,639 --> 01:49:00,199
Spoken like a true smart-ass.

1554
01:49:05,213 --> 01:49:08,205
What are you doing?
Are you eating my picture?

1555
01:49:19,594 --> 01:49:20,993
Let's get in the swing.

1556
01:49:21,563 --> 01:49:23,121
Get our feets in here.

1557
01:49:23,331 --> 01:49:24,161
There we go.

1558
01:49:24,799 --> 01:49:26,323
Hold on.

1559
01:49:35,310 --> 01:49:38,609
l don't know if this is
the right time or place...

1560
01:49:38,813 --> 01:49:40,440
...but l wanted to tell you...

1561
01:49:40,648 --> 01:49:43,640
...that Sammy and l have decided
if this baby's a girl...

1562
01:49:43,852 --> 01:49:45,820
...we'd like to name it Shelby...

1563
01:49:46,254 --> 01:49:49,485
...since she was the reason we met
in the first place.

1564
01:49:49,691 --> 01:49:50,919
lf you don't mind.

1565
01:49:51,126 --> 01:49:52,354
Shelby would love that.

1566
01:49:54,496 --> 01:49:56,157
l'm tickled pink.

1567
01:49:59,234 --> 01:50:00,223
Pink.

1568
01:50:00,802 --> 01:50:04,238
What are you gonna name it
if it happens to be a boy?

1569
01:50:05,440 --> 01:50:07,271
Shelby, l guess.

1570
01:50:08,143 --> 01:50:09,974
That's how it should be.

1571
01:50:10,378 --> 01:50:11,970
Life goes on.

1572
01:50:50,985 --> 01:50:53,749
l've never been so uncomfortable
in all my life.

1573
01:50:53,955 --> 01:50:57,755
We'll talk about ''uncomfortable''
when you're nine months pregnant.

1574
01:51:00,428 --> 01:51:03,363
Keep those eyes closed,
or l'll staple them shut.

1575
01:51:03,565 --> 01:51:05,726
-They're closed!
-Keep them closed.

1576
01:51:06,534 --> 01:51:07,967
-Now?
-Ready?

1577
01:51:10,805 --> 01:51:12,033
Keep them shut.

1578
01:51:12,574 --> 01:51:14,269
-Open them up.
-All right.

1579
01:51:16,811 --> 01:51:18,335
l don't believe it!

1580
01:51:18,546 --> 01:51:20,104
l'm a chain!

1581
01:51:24,652 --> 01:51:26,643
-Jesus!
-Lighten up.

1582
01:51:27,488 --> 01:51:29,956
Now, you just burst through
those bushes...

1583
01:51:30,158 --> 01:51:32,558
...and hop over to
where the kids are, okay?

1584
01:51:32,760 --> 01:51:35,058
What bushes? l can't see shit!

1585
01:51:35,263 --> 01:51:36,491
Over there.

1586
01:51:37,031 --> 01:51:38,430
''Over there.''

1587
01:51:38,633 --> 01:51:40,931
l'm an adult.
l'm not a 5-year-old!

1588
01:51:41,135 --> 01:51:44,298
On your mark. Get set. Go!

1589
01:51:45,073 --> 01:51:48,873
Okay, Jack, Jr.
l'm gonna tell you a story.

1590
01:51:51,012 --> 01:51:54,812
Once upon a time, there was
a beautiful young gal...

1591
01:51:55,016 --> 01:51:56,643
...named Shelby.

1592
01:51:57,252 --> 01:52:00,153
And Shelby had a lovely, kind...

1593
01:52:00,355 --> 01:52:04,189
...and wonderful good fairy named...

1594
01:52:04,392 --> 01:52:05,882
...Clairee.

1595
01:52:06,828 --> 01:52:09,319
But there was also a horrible...

1596
01:52:09,530 --> 01:52:12,499
...evil, ugly witch named...

1597
01:52:12,700 --> 01:52:13,894
...Ouiser.

1598
01:52:14,102 --> 01:52:16,570
l hate these stupid
neighborhood things.

1599
01:52:16,771 --> 01:52:19,262
No one's twisting your arm
to keep you here.

1600
01:52:19,474 --> 01:52:21,465
Well, l have to be sociable.

1601
01:52:23,544 --> 01:52:25,205
Rhett's here.

1602
01:52:27,582 --> 01:52:29,573
Let's connect the bald spots.

1603
01:52:31,486 --> 01:52:33,181
Eat shit and die.

1604
01:52:33,388 --> 01:52:34,218
Hello, M'Lynn.

1605
01:52:36,424 --> 01:52:38,790
Good to see you too, Ouiser, Owen.

1606
01:52:40,995 --> 01:52:42,758
Come on, Rhett! Kill, kill!

1607
01:52:42,964 --> 01:52:43,931
Quit it, Drum.

1608
01:52:44,132 --> 01:52:45,997
Stop egging him on.

1609
01:52:49,437 --> 01:52:52,736
And everyone lived happily ever after.

1610
01:52:53,741 --> 01:52:57,302
And the nasty, wicked,
evil, wretched...

1611
01:52:57,512 --> 01:53:00,276
...horrible, mean Ouiser...

1612
01:53:00,715 --> 01:53:03,013
...was never heard from again.

1613
01:53:03,751 --> 01:53:06,879
Now, it's almost time
for the Easter Bunny.

1614
01:53:07,088 --> 01:53:08,680
Run on down.

1615
01:53:24,605 --> 01:53:26,470
Hi, Jack! You remember me?

1616
01:53:26,841 --> 01:53:28,138
lt's your old pal Ouiser.

1617
01:53:33,281 --> 01:53:34,873
Just a second. lt's Jackson.

1618
01:53:35,383 --> 01:53:37,112
Jack, come here!

1619
01:53:46,961 --> 01:53:48,519
ls he all right?

1620
01:53:48,730 --> 01:53:50,493
Yes, he's all right.

1621
01:54:02,810 --> 01:54:04,778
Honey, it's okay. lt's okay.

1622
01:54:04,979 --> 01:54:07,607
Women have babies every day.

1623
01:54:07,815 --> 01:54:10,807
Jonathan, quick!
Get that Easter Bunny over here now.

1624
01:54:11,018 --> 01:54:12,952
-Tommy, where's Sammy?
-Over there.

1625
01:54:13,154 --> 01:54:15,179
-Excuse me.
-Why? What's going on?

1626
01:54:15,390 --> 01:54:18,848
Oh, my God! She's gonna have a baby.
Go get a doctor!

1627
01:54:19,060 --> 01:54:21,085
Help! A doctor!

1628
01:54:21,295 --> 01:54:22,785
This way, this way.

1629
01:54:26,167 --> 01:54:27,293
Get her in.

1630
01:54:29,237 --> 01:54:30,795
We'll find Sammy.

1631
01:54:32,073 --> 01:54:34,564
lt's all right, honey.
We'll get Sammy.

1632
01:54:49,557 --> 01:54:51,081
Come on, Sammy!

1633
01:54:52,427 --> 01:54:53,985
Get your tail hopping!

